Bodies of Photojournalists Killed in Libya Flown Out

-- B y   K a r l   S t a g n o - N a v a r r a
-- 
2011-04-24T04:05:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-23/bodies-of-photojournalists-killed-in-misrata-flown-to-malta.html
(Corrects date and recipient in second paragraph of story
originally published April 23. See EXTRA and MET for more on
unrest in the Middle East.)  The coffins carrying the bodies of
photojournalists Tim Hetherington and Chris Hondros, who were
killed by mortar shells in the Libyan city of Misrata, were
brought to Malta by a special military flight operated by the
U.S. government.  U.K. national Hetherington and American Hondros died April
20 during fighting between rebels and forces loyal to  Muammar Qaddafi . Hetherington had been nominated for an Academy Award
for a documentary on the war in  Afghanistan .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karl Stagno-Navarra at  ksnavarra@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 